Detailed Description

cvmx_agl_gmx_rx::_jabber

AGL_GMX_RX_JABBER = The max size packet after which GMX will truncate

Notes: CNT must be 8-byte aligned such that CNT[2:0] == 0

The packet that will be sent to the packet input logic will have an additionl 8 bytes if AGL_GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_CHK] is set and AGL_GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_STRP] is clear. The max packet that will be sent is defined as...

max_sized_packet = AGL_GMX_RX_JABBER[CNT]+((AGL_GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_CHK] & !AGL_GMX_RX_FRM_CTL[PRE_STRP])*8)

Be sure the CNT field value is at least as large as the AGL_GMX_RX_FRM_MAX[LEN] value. Failure to meet this constraint will cause packets that are within the AGL_GMX_RX_FRM_MAX[LEN] length to be rejected because they exceed the CNT limit.

Additionally reset when MIX<prt>_CTL[RESET] is set to 1.
